    <string name="menu_about">About</string>
    <string name="about_text">InterVene is a community safety mobile app that connects people who need help with nearby vigilantes (neighborhood watch volunteers).\nIt supports two complementary roles on a shared Google Maps interface.\n\nFor people at risk: users register a profile (alias, safe word, contact details) and can start a guided trip—sharing their live location while walking, with optional walking-route planning. A prominent !HELP! panic button triggers distress mode: an alarm sounds, a foreground service broadcasts the user\'s GPS position to Firebase (via GeoFire), and push notifications alert others nearby.\n\nFor responders: vigilantes register as individuals or groups, then start patrolling to publish their location in real time. They can view a distress list of active calls in the area and navigate to intervene.\n\nIn short, InterVene is a panic-button and neighborhood-watch coordination tool aimed at crime prevention and faster community response.</string>
